Dialogue: 1,0:00:00.00,0:00:05.48,英黑,,0,0,0,,All right, so I am a PhD student at The University of Alabama in Huntsville. There's a lot that goes into that.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:05.48,0:00:06.76,英黑,,0,0,0,,It's a very difficult thing for me.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:06.79,0:00:09.46,英黑,,0,0,0,,I'm studying under  Dr. Jason Cassibry. Really fun.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:09.48,0:00:16.24,英黑,,0,0,0,,The other day, someone from the university reaches out and they said, Hey, doesn't your student, Destin, doesn't he do talks occasionally or whatever?
Dialogue: 1,0:00:16.24,0:00:18.16,英黑,,0,0,0,,It was the American Astronautical Society.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:18.19,0:00:22.44,英黑,,0,0,0,,This is a group that discusses the future of space exploration, aerospace CEOs,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:22.47,0:00:25.28,英黑,,0,0,0,,industry leaders, students, government officials.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:25.31,0:00:28.38,英黑,,0,0,0,,They've been having these discussions since the 1950s.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:28.40,0:00:31.34,英黑,,0,0,0,,They asked if I would do what I call a talky talk.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:31.37,0:00:37.44,英黑,,0,0,0,,Now, usually I say no to talky talks because I like to prepare and get it right, and it just takes a long time.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:37.44,0:00:41.30,英黑,,0,0,0,,Plus, I only do a few of those a year, and I just didn't know if this was the right thing to do.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:41.32,0:00:48.52,英黑,,0,0,0,,But the more I got to thinking about it, the more I realized that the people that were going to be in this room are the movers and shakers in the aerospace industry.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:48.52,0:00:53.70,英黑,,0,0,0,,And these are the people that are doing things like planning the mission architecture to go back to the moon.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:53.73,0:01:01.02,英黑,,0,0,0,,And when I looked at the name of the talk, it was advancing space from Leo to Lunar and Beyond, or at least this is the symposium.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:01.05,0:01:04.88,英黑,,0,0,0,,It's the 2023 von Braun Space exploration symposium.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:04.91,0:01:14.10,英黑,,0,0,0,,Now, Werner von Braun, or von Braun, depending on what way you pronounce his name, was the main architect behind the Apollo program, which is when we went to the moon.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:14.13,0:01:17.76,英黑,,0,0,0,,Right now, America is doing what's called the Artemis program.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:17.79,0:01:24.62,英黑,,0,0,0,,The Artemis program is our effort to go back to the moon to take humans there now with new technology.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:24.64,0:01:25.66,英黑,,0,0,0,,It's very interesting.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:25.68,0:01:33.14,英黑,,0,0,0,,With most talky talks that I do, I like to provide an external perspective to the organization or the company that's asked me to come in and speak.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:33.17,0:01:38.54,英黑,,0,0,0,,In this case, all the people in front of me are the most important industry leaders in aerospace.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:38.57,0:01:45.21,英黑,,0,0,0,,I thought about what it would look like to take a third-party perspective view of Artemis.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:45.24,0:01:46.85,英黑,,0,0,0,,I thought that would be pretty good.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:46.88,0:01:53.88,英黑,,0,0,0,,But the more I started digging into Artemis, the more I realized there might be some issues in how people communicate about it.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:53.91,0:02:00.18,英黑,,0,0,0,,There's some architecture problems that people are unwilling to talk about these days because of how they got there politically.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:00.20,0:02:05.00,英黑,,0,0,0,,I was like, You know what? I just want to go say the thing that nobody's saying. That's what I decided to do.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:05.03,0:02:10.89,英黑,,0,0,0,,Now, a lot of people I respect, when I was doing my research and asking these questions, they said, Be careful, Destin.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:10.92,0:02:16.17,英黑,,0,0,0,,If you say certain things, this might change your relationship with NASA forever.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:16.20,0:02:22.10,英黑,,0,0,0,,I thought about it and I decided, You know what? This is the truth and this is what needs to be said.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:22.13,0:02:24.36,英黑,,0,0,0,,And NASA, please don't hate me.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:24.39,0:02:28.76,英黑,,0,0,0,,In all seriousness though, I'm nervous about this talk before I go in. You'll see that.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:28.79,0:02:32.52,英黑,,0,0,0,,I decided just to play the talk for you and let you see what this is like.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:32.55,0:02:36.66,英黑,,0,0,0,,Now, to be clear, being a YouTuber means nothing in this room.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:36.68,0:02:43.12,英黑,,0,0,0,,The first part of the talk is me trying to establish credibility within the aerospace industry by saying some of the things that I've done.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:43.15,0:02:49.18,英黑,,0,0,0,,I've done the Defense Acquisition University. I know what it means to develop a system that's going to be human-rated.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:49.21,0:02:51.06,英黑,,0,0,0,,I have to establish that.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:51.08,0:02:56.34,英黑,,0,0,0,,But also I have to sprinkle in a little of the, I'm the YouTuber guy who you think I am.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:56.37,0:02:59.48,英黑,,0,0,0,,And then in the end, I want to ask the difficult questions.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:59.51,0:03:02.90,英黑,,0,0,0,,So for me, this was an exercise in something called rhetoric.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:02.93,0:03:07.98,英黑,,0,0,0,,Rhetoric is trying to persuade somebody to a certain position, and that's what I was doing here.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:08.01,0:03:10.86,英黑,,0,0,0,,I thought you would enjoy being in the room.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:10.88,0:03:17.00,英黑,,0,0,0,,This is me in a room I usually wouldn't get to be in, and I thought you might like to peek in on this and see what I had to say.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:17.03,0:03:21.26,英黑,,0,0,0,,I would love to know what your thoughts are with my points about Artemis.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:21.28,0:03:22.50,英黑,,0,0,0,,That's it. We'll see how it works.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:22.53,0:03:23.40,英黑,,0,0,0,,I almost forgot.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:23.40,0:03:26.68,英黑,,0,0,0,,At some point, I'm going to show you this year's sticker design for patron.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:26.68,0:03:31.26,英黑,,0,0,0,,If you're interested in that, I think it's really cool. I'll show you that here in a bit.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:31.29,0:03:32.54,英黑,,0,0,0,,Anyway, on with the talk.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:32.57,0:03:36.94,英黑,,0,0,0,,We now get to get to our closing keynote for the day.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:36.97,0:03:44.42,英黑,,0,0,0,,We are really honored and pleased to have this speaker with us.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:44.45,0:03:48.22,英黑,,0,0,0,,He's no stranger talking to large audiences.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:48.25,0:03:56.90,英黑,,0,0,0,,Destin Sandlin is a husband, father, and aerospace engineer known for his educational video series, Smarter Every Day.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:56.93,0:03:59.90,英黑,,0,0,0,,He's also a current UAH student.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:59.93,0:04:04.08,英黑,,0,0,0,,So, Destin, I turn it over to you for you to talk. Thanks.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:06.00,0:04:07.78,英黑,,0,0,0,,Thank you. Hello.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:07.81,0:04:10.74,英黑,,0,0,0,,I'm seeing people I know. That's always good.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:10.77,0:04:15.11,英黑,,0,0,0,,My name is Destin, and when you leave here, what I'm hoping is that
Dialogue: 1,0:04:15.11,0:04:22.76,英黑,,0,0,0,,you'll look at the mission differently. In a world of talkers, you'll be a thinker and a doer and ask the hard questions.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:23.96,0:04:25.70,英黑,,0,0,0,,I've... Well, let's just do this.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:25.72,0:04:28.76,英黑,,0,0,0,,Who is this dude? It's a thing we do in Alabama.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:28.76,0:04:30.50,英黑,,0,0,0,,I know you guys from all over the place.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:30.53,0:04:33.56,英黑,,0,0,0,,Here in Alabama, we like to just... Can you hear me?
Dialogue: 1,0:04:33.59,0:04:35.02,英黑,,0,0,0,,Is this good? Okay.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:35.04,0:04:37.98,英黑,,0,0,0,,Here in Alabama, we're just low key, rednecks.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:38.01,0:04:39.82,英黑,,0,0,0,,You know that about us by now.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:39.84,0:04:42.18,英黑,,0,0,0,,I'll just go through who I am.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:42.21,0:04:46.68,英黑,,0,0,0,,I grew up across the river and just a Redneck kid.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:46.71,0:04:50.24,英黑,,0,0,0,,That's me and my big dog, Thunder. My dad's over there.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:50.27,0:04:52.86,英黑,,0,0,0,,Dad, you can come up here and sit down if you want.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:52.89,0:04:55.94,英黑,,0,0,0,,You're okay? Yeah, dad's here.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:55.97,0:04:57.74,英黑,,0,0,0,,Yeah, dad's awesome. [Audience applaudes]
Dialogue: 1,0:05:01.32,0:05:07.98,英黑,,0,0,0,,I grew up just a normal kid, and my grandfather, my dad's dad, worked at this little outfit called the Army Ballistic Missile Agency.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:08.01,0:05:11.42,英黑,,0,0,0,,Have you ever heard of it? Yeah, you heard of it? Yeah, it's pretty good.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:11.45,0:05:17.22,英黑,,0,0,0,,His name was Pryor Wilson Sandlin, [Audience laughs] Why do people always laugh when I show this slide?
Dialogue: 1,0:05:17.24,0:05:19.84,英黑,,0,0,0,,Every time I show my grandfather. They're like, Ha ha ha.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:19.84,0:05:23.74,英黑,,0,0,0,,I was like, I don't understand. This is how I grew up. It's a culture thing, I guess.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:23.76,0:05:30.16,英黑,,0,0,0,,But my grandfather, same guy that taught me how to shoot a squirrel out of a tree, a guy that taught me all kinds of stuff...
Dialogue: 1,0:05:30.16,0:05:34.52,英黑,,0,0,0,,I mean, he taught me about science and he would take me outside and he would show me stuff.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:34.52,0:05:39.30,英黑,,0,0,0,,I remember Granddaddy didn't, I don't know if you remember this dad, but Granddaddy didn't tell me he loved me.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:39.33,0:05:40.74,英黑,,0,0,0,,He didn't say that.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:40.77,0:05:45.06,英黑,,0,0,0,,He said, "Boy, I love you to the Comet Belt."
Dialogue: 1,0:05:45.09,0:05:48.58,英黑,,0,0,0,,I was like, What the heck does that mean? I don't know what that means.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:48.60,0:05:55.56,英黑,,0,0,0,,Then years later, I was sitting here in the halls of UAH, pencil-whipping some stuff, and I was calculating the Delta V requirements to go to Mars.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:55.59,0:06:01.82,英黑,,0,0,0,,I was like, You know? Not only is it probable or possible that we're going to go to Mars, it's going to happen.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:01.85,0:06:05.92,英黑,,0,0,0,,He loves me out beyond that. I know this is the asteroid belt, not the comet belt.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:05.92,0:06:07.74,英黑,,0,0,0,,I have to say this because you guys are smart.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:07.77,0:06:10.36,英黑,,0,0,0,,But granddaddy used to say things like that.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:10.39,0:06:21.90,英黑,,0,0,0,,The same person that made me feel really, really small and made me want to outwit a squirrel, was the same guy that made me think about how big the universe was.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:21.92,0:06:25.01,英黑,,0,0,0,,It's just how we grew up here in Alabama. It's great. I love it.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:25.01,0:06:27.62,英黑,,0,0,0,,I went to University of Alabama.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:27.65,0:06:31.96,英黑,,0,0,0,,I learned a lot from Darryl Sandlin right there who worked on the James Webb Space Telescope.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:31.98,0:06:37.94,英黑,,0,0,0,,That's a picture of dad when he was doing metrology on the SunShields for the James Webb Space Telescope.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:37.97,0:06:39.62,英黑,,0,0,0,,Really cool stuff.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:39.65,0:06:48.38,英黑,,0,0,0,,Dad used to moonlight as a CMM operator and programmer, and he used to teach me stuff about coordinate transformations before I knew what algebra was.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:48.41,0:06:50.72,英黑,,0,0,0,,I had a really neat upbringing.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:50.72,0:06:54.66,英黑,,0,0,0,,I had internships at the University of Alabama. I worked at Eaton, aerospace.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:54.68,0:07:03.06,英黑,,0,0,0,,The cool thing about that is the test cell next to me, I was working on the Joint Strike Fighters fuel pump, which was also the hydraulic pump, really neat thing.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:03.09,0:07:05.38,英黑,,0,0,0,,I used to test lubricity on that thing.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:05.41,0:07:10.50,英黑,,0,0,0,,But in the cell right next to me was the SR-71 fuel pump test cell.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:10.53,0:07:12.54,英黑,,0,0,0,,It was designed to explode.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:12.57,0:07:15.98,英黑,,0,0,0,,They told me, they're in Jackson, Mississippi, they said, Yeah.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:16.01,0:07:23.42,英黑,,0,0,0,,These dudes showed up and they're like, All right, we need a fuel pump that needs to do this flow rate and this pressure.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:23.45,0:07:27.02,英黑,,0,0,0,,The Mississippi boys were like, Nothing needs a fuel pump like that.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:27.04,0:07:29.74,英黑,,0,0,0,,They're like, Build it. [Audience Laughs]
Dialogue: 1,0:07:29.77,0:07:31.84,英黑,,0,0,0,,That's the coolest story ever.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:31.86,0:07:34.12,英黑,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I also worked at Little Debbie Snack Cakes,
Dialogue: 1,0:07:34.15,0:07:38.86,英黑,,0,0,0,,basically the same level of, Why are you laughing at me?
Dialogue: 1,0:07:38.89,0:07:40.18,英黑,,0,0,0,,Little Debbie is awesome.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:40.20,0:07:41.30,英黑,,0,0,0,,Let me tell you about Little Debbie.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:41.33,0:07:46.10,英黑,,0,0,0,,Imagine this is a sheet of zebra cakes right here. It's moving along.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:46.13,0:07:50.78,英黑,,0,0,0,,You have a double guillotine striking that thing as it moves along. That's great.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:50.80,0:07:52.36,英黑,,0,0,0,,How do you get the chocolate drizzle on there?
Dialogue: 1,0:07:52.36,0:07:59.02,英黑,,0,0,0,,You just flip on this little switch and the little motor starts turning and the chocolate drizzle starts coming out and you get a sign wave on top of your cakes.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:59.04,0:08:00.90,英黑,,0,0,0,,But wait, there's more.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:00.92,0:08:07.98,英黑,,0,0,0,,Flip another mechanical lever, you throw in the cosine, the other, you get it out of phase, it makes a circle.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:08.84,0:08:13.79,英黑,,0,0,0,,That's how they do the fancy cakes. They do zebra cakes and fancy cakes on the same line. It's incredible.[Audience Laughs]
Dialogue: 1,0:08:14.77,0:08:17.30,英黑,,0,0,0,,I'm wasting time. Let's keep going.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:17.33,0:08:21.58,英黑,,0,0,0,,That was where I met my wife. Check this out, isn't she hot? [Audience Laughs]
Dialogue: 1,0:08:22.56,0:08:25.46,英黑,,0,0,0,,My wife's really pretty too. You see my wife? She's great.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:25.46,0:08:30.50,英黑,,0,0,0,, My wife and I, we have four kids and we love them and we think we're going to keep them.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:30.53,0:08:40.50,英黑,,0,0,0,,Right here, this is my upbringing as a professional. I worked across the interstate here in a place called Redstone Test Center.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:40.53,0:08:45.82,英黑,,0,0,0,,The thing think on the left is a component for something called an active protection system.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:45.84,0:08:52.26,英黑,,0,0,0,,We were trying to defeat rocket-propelled Grenades as they were fired at vehicles in Iraq and Afghanistan.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:52.28,0:08:53.50,英黑,,0,0,0,,I spent a lot of time on that.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:53.53,0:08:57.54,英黑,,0,0,0,,Maybe in 25 years, we can talk about that. But it's really cool.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:57.56,0:08:59.60,英黑,,0,0,0,,On the right, I worked missiles for a long time.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:59.60,0:09:03.88,英黑,,0,0,0,,On the right, I went after a while and I was like, I'm going to go work on aircraft because I don't know aircraft.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:03.91,0:09:06.52,英黑,,0,0,0,,I can't speak that language. I learned a lot there.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:06.52,0:09:11.56,英黑,,0,0,0,,The cool thing about ATEC, Army Test Evaluation Command, we were in the developmental test command.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:11.58,0:09:18.42,英黑,,0,0,0,,We were helping acquire material for the army, material that would be used by soldiers.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:18.44,0:09:21.90,英黑,,0,0,0,,Human rating of products was huge.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:21.93,0:09:29.58,英黑,,0,0,0,,I had to go through what's called the Defense Acquisition University. I get what it's like to human rate a product. It's a big deal.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:29.61,0:09:33.46,英黑,,0,0,0,,I'm just giving you that to say like, Yeah, you tip gaha, funny.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:33.49,0:09:37.82,英黑,,0,0,0,,Also, a little bit of experience in the field here.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:37.85,0:09:39.82,英黑,,0,0,0,,This is a cool thing.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:39.85,0:09:43.38,英黑,,0,0,0,,This is what we would call at the range Tuesday.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:43.41,0:09:48.96,英黑,,0,0,0,,Three, two, one, fire.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:53.76,0:09:56.74,英黑,,0,0,0,,A lot of people don't know, we test Javelin here.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:56.77,0:10:03.22,英黑,,0,0,0,,I remember a very specific moment. We had just blown up a Russian tank.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:03.25,0:10:07.72,英黑,,0,0,0,,I remember the smell. I just remember a lot of things.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:07.75,0:10:13.51,英黑,,0,0,0,,We've gone down and I'm living my best life, scoring the target, looking at the shape charge penetration in the hole.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:13.77,0:10:22.14,英黑,,0,0,0,,I look at Tracy Williams, who's a Vietnam veteran, who helped develop Javelin for when it was called All Zem, if you know about that.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:22.16,0:10:26.74,英黑,,0,0,0,,He helped develop it. He fought in the Vietnam War.
