Dialogue: 1,0:12:29.89,0:12:32.34,英黑,,0,0,0,,But this is not what I was thinking.
Dialogue: 1,0:12:32.36,0:12:36.34,英黑,,0,0,0,,In the moment, I was like, I'm going to upload this to the internet because it's amazing.
Dialogue: 1,0:12:36.37,0:12:46.90,英黑,,0,0,0,,This is amazing because there is clearly a closed loop control system here that [Audience Laughs] appears to be optically coupled to this chicken. I'm back driving it.
Dialogue: 1,0:12:46.92,0:12:49.74,英黑,,0,0,0,,You know why chickens do this, by the way? Do you know this?
Dialogue: 1,0:12:50.80,0:12:54.02,英黑,,0,0,0,,This is the smartest room I've ever talked to. Nobody knows this.
Dialogue: 1,0:12:54.04,0:12:57.46,英黑,,0,0,0,,Okay, so basically there's this thing called the vestibula ocular reflex.
Dialogue: 1,0:12:57.48,0:12:59.78,英黑,,0,0,0,,Do you know about it? Everybody look at my hand.
Dialogue: 1,0:12:59.81,0:13:02.38,英黑,,0,0,0,,I'm going to move my hand. Track my hand.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:02.40,0:13:04.38,英黑,,0,0,0,,Okay, birds have a hard time doing that.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:04.40,0:13:09.94,英黑,,0,0,0,,What they do is they lock their head and that's the reference frame, and then they walk under it and it ends up looking like this.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:09.97,0:13:15.90,英黑,,0,0,0,,They'll walk and then they'll walk under it. They'll throw their head, and it makes sense now?
Dialogue: 1,0:13:15.93,0:13:17.94,英黑,,0,0,0,,That's what they do.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:17.97,0:13:23.22,英黑,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so when whoops! [Audience Laughs] that's great.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:23.25,0:13:27.82,英黑,,0,0,0,,Basically, what's happening is I'm uploading this to the internet and I'm like, Man, I'm in the thinky place.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:27.85,0:13:30.86,英黑,,0,0,0,,I'm really smart and I'm proud of myself for how smart I am.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:30.89,0:13:34.22,英黑,,0,0,0,,Then what does the internet do with this?
Dialogue: 1,0:13:34.25,0:13:38.14,英黑,,0,0,0,,Hey, look at this red neck playing with a chicken on the internet.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:38.16,0:13:41.76,英黑,,0,0,0,,He'll take that thing and he'll move it like this and that head stays right there.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:41.79,0:13:46.52,英黑,,0,0,0,,I'm like, No, no, no, no, no, no, no, no, no. No, no, no. I'm smart, I promise.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:46.52,0:13:47.80,英黑,,0,0,0,,I'm trying to be smart about this.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:47.83,0:13:51.44,英黑,,0,0,0,,They're like, No, man, that chicken wiggle so weird.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:51.52,0:13:53.62,英黑,,0,0,0,,I was like, Not like this.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:54.80,0:13:57.31,英黑,,0,0,0,,But then after that, something happened.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:57.85,0:14:01.24,英黑,,0,0,0,,I got to think about things. This grew into Smarter Every Day.
Dialogue: 1,0:14:01.24,0:14:07.58,英黑,,0,0,0,,The reason it grew into Smarter Every Day is my dad made me take a business minor class, honestly, that was part of it.
Dialogue: 1,0:14:07.61,0:14:16.40,英黑,,0,0,0,,But one of the things I did is I reevaluated how I looked at how I communicate with people.
Dialogue: 1,0:14:16.43,0:14:21.62,英黑,,0,0,0,,Basically, I decided, You know what I'm going to do? I'm going to do this.
Dialogue: 1,0:14:21.64,0:14:25.30,英黑,,0,0,0,,I'm going to take my videos, which I create called PennyWhistle Productions,
Dialogue: 1,0:14:25.32,0:14:27.72,英黑,,0,0,0,,I'm going to brand it because dad made me take a marketing class.
Dialogue: 1,0:14:27.72,0:14:29.46,英黑,,0,0,0,,I'm going to call it Smarter Every Day.
Dialogue: 1,0:14:29.49,0:14:36.56,英黑,,0,0,0,,I'm going to focus on quality over quantity, and I just basically engineered it. That's all I did.
Dialogue: 1,0:14:37.06,0:14:39.42,英黑,,0,0,0,,And this happened. This is another thing I did.
Dialogue: 1,0:14:39.45,0:14:45.22,英黑,,0,0,0,,I said, Every video I make, I'm going to be deliberate about how I execute the video.
Dialogue: 1,0:14:45.25,0:14:50.78,英黑,,0,0,0,,I'm going to start the video with incredibly high personality. It's going to be fun.
Dialogue: 1,0:14:50.80,0:14:55.02,英黑,,0,0,0,,I'm going to tell you about chickens and you're going to like it because chickens.
Dialogue: 1,0:14:55.51,0:15:01.06,英黑,,0,0,0,,Then slowly I'm going to ramp down the personality over time and I'll ramp up the topical complexity.
Dialogue: 1,0:15:01.53,0:15:06.74,英黑,,0,0,0,,When you ramp up that topical complexity, then people walk up that mountain with you
Dialogue: 1,0:15:06.77,0:15:10.70,英黑,,0,0,0,,because it's not like, Hey, zero to a hundred instantly.
Dialogue: 1,0:15:10.72,0:15:13.56,英黑,,0,0,0,,Let's talk about the sheer, let's talk about mohr's circle right now.
Dialogue: 1,0:15:13.58,0:15:18.30,英黑,,0,0,0,,No, we're just going to slowly ramp up the mountain together.
Dialogue: 1,0:15:18.32,0:15:22.74,英黑,,0,0,0,,Then towards the end of the interaction, I ramp down before people get bored and scared.
Dialogue: 1,0:15:22.76,0:15:25.02,英黑,,0,0,0,,Kind of like right now, it's getting weird right here.
Dialogue: 1,0:15:25.05,0:15:29.90,英黑,,0,0,0,,I ramp it down and then we land the plane. I'm going to do that with my videos.
Dialogue: 1,0:15:29.90,0:15:32.74,英黑,,0,0,0,,And it worked. It worked very, very well.
Dialogue: 1,0:15:32.77,0:15:34.92,英黑,,0,0,0,,That was really, really cool.
Dialogue: 1,0:15:35.88,0:15:39.08,英黑,,0,0,0,,If only going to the moon were that easy.
Dialogue: 1,0:15:39.68,0:15:45.34,英黑,,0,0,0,,Let's just get a plan. Let's write it down. Let's award some contracts and let's do it.
Dialogue: 1,0:15:46.60,0:15:49.26,英黑,,0,0,0,,If only your job were that easy.
Dialogue: 1,0:15:49.29,0:15:52.02,英黑,,0,0,0,,Why is it so difficult to do what you do?
Dialogue: 1,0:15:52.05,0:15:56.22,英黑,,0,0,0,,My assumption here is that I'm talking to a room full of policymakers,
Dialogue: 1,0:15:56.22,0:16:01.08,英黑,,0,0,0,,intelligent people that are going to shape the future of human space flight. Is that correct? [crickets]
Dialogue: 1,0:16:02.20,0:16:03.96,英黑,,0,0,0,,Somebody talk to me.
Dialogue: 1,0:16:04.60,0:16:06.14,英黑,,0,0,0,,Engineers, program managers.
Dialogue: 1,0:16:06.16,0:16:10.74,英黑,,0,0,0,,Yeah, this is the event where you get to put on literally your fancy pants and come hang out together, right?
Dialogue: 1,0:16:10.77,0:16:15.50,英黑,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I heard about the ball or whatever you guys did. Very nice. [Audience Laughs]
Dialogue: 1,0:16:15.53,0:16:20.94,英黑,,0,0,0,,One of the reasons why things get difficult is politics.
Dialogue: 1,0:16:22.42,0:16:25.98,英黑,,0,0,0,,Politics, I learned this firsthand.
Dialogue: 1,0:16:26.12,0:16:28.18,英黑,,0,0,0,,You remember where this started, by the way, the chicken thing?
Dialogue: 1,0:16:28.20,0:16:29.82,英黑,,0,0,0,,Well, somehow it ended up here.
Dialogue: 1,0:16:30.27,0:16:33.14,英黑,,0,0,0,,I don't know how that happened. Somehow it ended up here.
Dialogue: 1,0:16:33.17,0:16:40.90,英黑,,0,0,0,,What I learned in this moment is here in Huntsville, I was like, Hey, I'm going to go talk to the President.
Dialogue: 1,0:16:40.92,0:16:45.50,英黑,,0,0,0,,Hey, John, what do you think I should ask the President? I get three questions. What should I ask?
Dialogue: 1,0:16:45.50,0:16:51.52,英黑,,0,0,0,,John's over there. [In Southern Accent] He's like, I'll tell you what I'd tell him.
Dialogue: 1,0:16:53.00,0:16:55.34,英黑,,0,0,0,,I'm like, Yeah, what is that?
Dialogue: 1,0:16:55.37,0:16:58.52,英黑,,0,0,0,,[Accent again] He ain't going to take my guns. [Audience Laughs]
Dialogue: 1,0:16:58.64,0:17:05.00,英黑,,0,0,0,,I'm like, John, here's the deal, buddy. This is literally going to happen. I'm literally going to talk to the President.
Dialogue: 1,0:17:05.00,0:17:08.01,英黑,,0,0,0,,I don't think I'm going to win friends and influence people if I do that.
Dialogue: 1,0:17:08.04,0:17:11.50,英黑,,0,0,0,,We got to like, That's not going to work.
Dialogue: 1,0:17:11.52,0:17:13.14,英黑,,0,0,0,,Politics, you got to communicate.
Dialogue: 1,0:17:13.16,0:17:16.05,英黑,,0,0,0,,One of the things I did, and I'm going to burn this because of time too.
Dialogue: 1,0:17:16.08,0:17:20.29,英黑,,0,0,0,,One of the things I did is I talked to him about political discourse.
Dialogue: 1,0:17:20.32,0:17:21.18,英黑,,0,0,0,,You know what? I'm not burning it.
Dialogue: 1,0:17:21.20,0:17:23.76,英黑,,0,0,0,,Let's go. Let's see.
Dialogue: 1,0:17:23.80,0:17:29.50,英黑,,0,0,0,,I decided to ask the first question on how he gets smarter on topics he might not be the expert on.
Dialogue: 1,0:17:29.52,0:17:34.14,英黑,,0,0,0,,It was an interesting answer because it's clear that he's changed his methods over the course of his presidency.
Dialogue: 1,0:17:34.16,0:17:37.46,英黑,,0,0,0,,As he was answering this question, it was pretty clear to me that he was in interview mode.
Dialogue: 1,0:17:37.48,0:17:39.04,英黑,,0,0,0,,His body language was a little rigid.
Dialogue: 1,0:17:39.04,0:17:43.90,英黑,,0,0,0,,Now, keep in mind that at this point, the president still doesn't know what interviewer I'm going to be.
Dialogue: 1,0:17:43.92,0:17:45.53,英黑,,0,0,0,,For all he knows, I could be hostile.
Dialogue: 1,0:17:45.56,0:17:48.57,英黑,,0,0,0,,What happened next was a moment I will never forget.
Dialogue: 1,0:17:48.60,0:17:53.18,英黑,,0,0,0,,I knew before he did that we were both on the same wavelength, and I really wanted to let him know that.
Dialogue: 1,0:17:53.20,0:17:56.29,英黑,,0,0,0,,After all, I had listened to him already for 10 hours via audiobook.
Dialogue: 1,0:17:56.32,0:18:00.94,英黑,,0,0,0,,If you watch the President's face, you can see the exact moment that we connect.
Dialogue: 1,0:18:00.96,0:18:05.90,英黑,,0,0,0,,And that, I think, is pretty consistent with how scientists approach problems in general.
Dialogue: 1,0:18:05.92,0:18:08.66,英黑,,0,0,0,,Now, I actually knew that about you because I've listened to your audiobooks.
Dialogue: 1,0:18:08.69,0:18:15.05,英黑,,0,0,0,,And in Dreams of My Father, it ended with the 2004 Democratic National Convention speech.
Dialogue: 1,0:18:15.05,0:18:17.50,英黑,,0,0,0,,Did you see it? Let's back it up and watch his body language.
Dialogue: 1,0:18:17.53,0:18:21.09,英黑,,0,0,0,,He's a little guarded and then the connection. Isn't that cool?
Dialogue: 1,0:18:21.12,0:18:28.76,英黑,,0,0,0,,It's the exact moment that this quit being an interview and became a fun, intelligent conversation between two individuals who want the best for each other.
Dialogue: 1,0:18:28.76,0:18:31.90,英黑,,0,0,0,,It was a really cool moment. And I won't forget it.
Dialogue: 1,0:18:31.92,0:18:37.07,英黑,,0,0,0,,Okay, so the President went on to explain some really interesting things, and he talked about negative feedback
Dialogue: 1,0:18:37.07,0:18:41.44,英黑,,0,0,0,,and how we as a society have lost the ability to provide negative feedback to each other.
Dialogue: 1,0:18:41.84,0:18:46.32,英黑,,0,0,0,,Because why? [Zero response from audience...]
Dialogue: 1,0:18:46.92,0:18:49.14,英黑,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you guys are... This is the thing.
Dialogue: 1,0:18:49.17,0:18:51.91,英黑,,0,0,0,,You're scared to even talk right now. [Audience Laughs]
Dialogue: 1,0:18:52.10,0:18:53.33,英黑,,0,0,0,,I'm not joking.
Dialogue: 1,0:18:53.36,0:18:55.80,英黑,,0,0,0,,You're terrified to talk right now.
Dialogue: 1,0:18:56.18,0:18:58.68,英黑,,0,0,0,,That's a problem. That's a problem.
Dialogue: 1,0:18:58.71,0:19:02.40,英黑,,0,0,0,,You know the truth and you're afraid to say it.
Dialogue: 1,0:19:03.24,0:19:04.90,英黑,,0,0,0,,I'm Destin, have a good day.
Dialogue: 1,0:19:04.93,0:19:09.25,英黑,,0,0,0,,No, the deal is we know things and we're afraid to say it.
Dialogue: 1,0:19:09.28,0:19:15.25,英黑,,0,0,0,,Why is that? Because we know the other side is going to fight or we might get canceled or whatever is happening today in your office.
Dialogue: 1,0:19:15.28,0:19:17.29,英黑,,0,0,0,,I totally get it.
Dialogue: 1,0:19:17.32,0:19:19.98,英黑,,0,0,0,,But we're engineers, right?
Dialogue: 1,0:19:20.36,0:19:23.18,英黑,,0,0,0,,Engineers know what this is, don't they?
Dialogue: 1,0:19:23.20,0:19:25.42,英黑,,0,0,0,,Young engineers on the front row. What is this?
Dialogue: 1,0:19:25.45,0:19:27.77,英黑,,0,0,0,,[Audience memeber] PID! PID control loop.
Dialogue: 1,0:19:27.80,0:19:29.50,英黑,,0,0,0,,Rock and roll. That's what I'm talking about.
Dialogue: 1,0:19:29.53,0:19:32.80,英黑,,0,0,0,,What's an important part of the PID control loop?
Dialogue: 1,0:19:34.00,0:19:39.00,英黑,,0,0,0,,Let's ignore the letters. Let's go up here to the little summation symbol on the top right.
Dialogue: 1,0:19:39.00,0:19:42.20,英黑,,0,0,0,,You got a plus and a minus. What does that mean? [Audience] Feedback.
Dialogue: 1,0:19:42.23,0:19:44.22,英黑,,0,0,0,,Feedback. Right.
Dialogue: 1,0:19:44.24,0:19:46.12,英黑,,0,0,0,,Feedback is important to any engineer.
Dialogue: 1,0:19:46.15,0:19:51.05,英黑,,0,0,0,,If you have only positive feedback in the system, what happens to it?
Dialogue: 1,0:19:53.52,0:19:54.92,英黑,,0,0,0,,It goes unstable.
Dialogue: 1,0:19:54.92,0:19:57.86,英黑,,0,0,0,,Is this political science?
Dialogue: 1,0:19:57.89,0:19:59.70,英黑,,0,0,0,,This is math, right?
Dialogue: 1,0:19:59.72,0:20:01.22,英黑,,0,0,0,,It also works with political science.
Dialogue: 1,0:20:01.24,0:20:09.77,英黑,,0,0,0,,But it's really interesting. If you don't have positive and negative feedback in any system, it goes unstable and chaotic and things explode and break and it's bad, right?
Dialogue: 1,0:20:09.80,0:20:13.55,英黑,,0,0,0,,We know this to be true because whatever your degree is.
Dialogue: 1,0:20:13.55,0:20:17.60,英黑,,0,0,0,,I think it's important for negative feedback. I'm grateful that I learned that.
Dialogue: 1,0:20:17.63,0:20:21.81,英黑,,0,0,0,,I also asked the President about his plans for deep space exploration at the time.
Dialogue: 1,0:20:21.84,0:20:27.53,英黑,,0,0,0,,Personally, I'm going to say this because it's an opinion I have and I'm allowed to have opinions.
Dialogue: 1,0:20:27.56,0:20:30.46,英黑,,0,0,0,,I was unsatisfied with his answer at the time.
