Dialogue: 1,0:31:29.65,0:31:32.40,英黑,,0,0,0,,The fact that we have this very complex architecture
Dialogue: 1,0:31:32.40,0:31:37.10,英黑,,0,0,0,,and we don't know the exact answer to such a big question
Dialogue: 1,0:31:37.10,0:31:44.50,英黑,,0,0,0,,is pretty damning because if we don't know such a simple answer to a big question, what does that say about the little things?
Dialogue: 1,0:31:44.53,0:31:48.38,英黑,,0,0,0,,When my grandfather was sipping coffee out of this mug down the road,
Dialogue: 1,0:31:48.38,0:31:52.26,英黑,,0,0,0,,they had quarterly reports on every little component of what was going on,
Dialogue: 1,0:31:52.26,0:31:57.33,英黑,,0,0,0,,down to the pressure transducers at some subcontractor at a small plant somewhere in America.
Dialogue: 1,0:31:57.36,0:32:04.18,英黑,,0,0,0,,They knew what was going to happen because the more complex the system is, the more communication you need to make it work.
Dialogue: 1,0:32:04.21,0:32:07.56,英黑,,0,0,0,,Saturn V quarterly film report number seven.
Dialogue: 1,0:32:07.59,0:32:10.33,英黑,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 1,0:32:10.36,0:32:16.85,英黑,,0,0,0,,I think there's a problem because right now we are two years out from this launch and we don't know the number of rockets.
Dialogue: 1,0:32:16.96,0:32:20.02,英黑,,0,0,0,,I don't think that means we're going to launch to this thing in two years.
Dialogue: 1,0:32:20.05,0:32:22.80,英黑,,0,0,0,,I'm just saying it. That's where I'm at as an engineer.
Dialogue: 1,0:32:22.83,0:32:27.42,英黑,,0,0,0,,It's time to be honest. As engineers, we are not known to be effective communicators.
Dialogue: 1,0:32:27.45,0:32:29.74,英黑,,0,0,0,,That's just not a strong suit of an engineer.
Dialogue: 1,0:32:29.77,0:32:38.70,英黑,,0,0,0,,It is time to lay out and systematize the communication so that every organization that's involved knows far more information than they need.
Dialogue: 1,0:32:38.73,0:32:42.31,英黑,,0,0,0,,We have actual targets and dates that are actionable
Dialogue: 1,0:32:42.31,0:32:48.34,英黑,,0,0,0,,and they don't depend on a miracle in technological innovation occurring at some point on the Gantt chart.
Dialogue: 1,0:32:48.49,0:32:52.46,英黑,,0,0,0,,We actually have actionable things that have to happen in certain time frames.
Dialogue: 1,0:32:52.49,0:32:56.07,英黑,,0,0,0,,And if something doesn't happen, a critical technology isn't development,
Dialogue: 1,0:32:56.07,0:32:59.05,英黑,,0,0,0,,we communicate that there's a schedule slip to everyone.
Dialogue: 1,0:32:59.08,0:33:04.39,英黑,,0,0,0,,The fact that it still says two years till this launch tells me that we have a communication issue,
Dialogue: 1,0:33:04.39,0:33:09.02,英黑,,0,0,0,,and I would like for that to be resolved by centralized leadership.
Dialogue: 1,0:33:09.24,0:33:10.44,英黑,,0,0,0,,There, I said my thing.
Dialogue: 1,0:33:10.47,0:33:15.32,英黑,,0,0,0,,Okay, so at this point, you will see a shift in the tone of the talk.
Dialogue: 1,0:33:15.35,0:33:16.98,英黑,,0,0,0,,I've laid out the problem.
Dialogue: 1,0:33:17.01,0:33:20.16,英黑,,0,0,0,,Now I'm going to transition towards aspirational goals.
Dialogue: 1,0:33:20.19,0:33:21.66,英黑,,0,0,0,,How do we get there?
Dialogue: 1,0:33:21.69,0:33:26.42,英黑,,0,0,0,,And it's going to hinge a lot upon this. What made Apollo a success?
Dialogue: 1,0:33:26.45,0:33:30.18,英黑,,0,0,0,,And you'll see me talk about that later here in the talk.
Dialogue: 1,0:33:30.52,0:33:34.42,英黑,,0,0,0,,Remember what I said earlier about the importance of negative feedback.
Dialogue: 1,0:33:34.45,0:33:38.14,英黑,,0,0,0,,I am but a simple Redneck, Alabama, engineer.
Dialogue: 1,0:33:38.96,0:33:41.66,英黑,,0,0,0,,But for real, here's the deal.
Dialogue: 1,0:33:41.69,0:33:43.28,英黑,,0,0,0,,We're going.
Dialogue: 1,0:33:43.96,0:33:46.68,英黑,,0,0,0,,We've selected this architecture.
Dialogue: 1,0:33:47.22,0:33:48.98,英黑,,0,0,0,,So how do we make it work?
Dialogue: 1,0:33:49.01,0:33:53.52,英黑,,0,0,0,,I'm going to accept the contracts are written.
Dialogue: 1,0:33:54.04,0:33:58.62,英黑,,0,0,0,,We have European partners that are building the first node for Gateway.
Dialogue: 1,0:33:59.16,0:34:02.00,英黑,,0,0,0,,I'm going to accept it right now. Let's say everybody in the room accepts it.
Dialogue: 1,0:34:02.00,0:34:05.38,英黑,,0,0,0,,We're going, we're going to be unified and we're going to make it happen.
Dialogue: 1,0:34:05.38,0:34:10.13,英黑,,0,0,0,,Now, what do you do with that information? What do you do with that information?
Dialogue: 1,0:34:10.39,0:34:13.82,英黑,,0,0,0,,I think the key is to learn lessons from the past.
Dialogue: 1,0:34:14.99,0:34:17.38,英黑,,0,0,0,,Who is this person? Joseph Shea.
Dialogue: 1,0:34:19.72,0:34:21.42,英黑,,0,0,0,,He's a very, very important person.
Dialogue: 1,0:34:21.45,0:34:24.06,英黑,,0,0,0,,This story, I'm about to tell you, is sad.
Dialogue: 1,0:34:24.09,0:34:29.68,英黑,,0,0,0,,Joseph Shea is sitting in a meeting here in the '60s in a presentation.
Dialogue: 1,0:34:29.68,0:34:32.98,英黑,,0,0,0,,If you're in the airspace industry, you're in meetings all day long.
Dialogue: 1,0:34:33.01,0:34:36.24,英黑,,0,0,0,,That's what you do. That's what this guy is doing right now.
Dialogue: 1,0:34:37.32,0:34:38.65,英黑,,0,0,0,,Who are these people?
Dialogue: 1,0:34:40.39,0:34:41.30,英黑,,0,0,0,,Apollo 1.
Dialogue: 1,0:34:41.37,0:34:46.85,英黑,,0,0,0,,Yeah, there's a high school here in Huntsville named Grissom, after the gentleman on the left there.
Dialogue: 1,0:34:47.02,0:34:52.64,英黑,,0,0,0,,These astronauts were getting ready for Apollo 1, and they knew there were problems with the capsule.
Dialogue: 1,0:34:52.67,0:34:54.17,英黑,,0,0,0,,They knew this.
Dialogue: 1,0:34:54.20,0:34:59.62,英黑,,0,0,0,,The engineer team knew there were problems with the capsule. Everybody was working feverishly to figure it out.
Dialogue: 1,0:34:59.65,0:35:02.69,英黑,,0,0,0,,Everybody was trying to figure this out.
Dialogue: 1,0:35:03.29,0:35:12.21,英黑,,0,0,0,,Then on January 27th, 1967, a travesty happened.
Dialogue: 1,0:35:12.24,0:35:14.85,英黑,,0,0,0,,There was an accident on the pad.
Dialogue: 1,0:35:15.31,0:35:21.28,英黑,,0,0,0,,The capsule burned because they were in a 100% oxygen environment, a flame started by Gus Grissom's seat.
Dialogue: 1,0:35:21.42,0:35:22.51,英黑,,0,0,0,,They died.
Dialogue: 1,0:35:22.64,0:35:25.16,英黑,,0,0,0,,I remember being at a family get-together years ago.
Dialogue: 1,0:35:25.19,0:35:33.56,英黑,,0,0,0,,My grandfather worked over at NASA, and I remember hearing the old timers talk about that fire with deep sadness and reverence.
Dialogue: 1,0:35:33.93,0:35:39.43,英黑,,0,0,0,,It occurred to me that something changed about NASA in that moment.
Dialogue: 1,0:35:39.61,0:35:47.04,英黑,,0,0,0,,It changed in the middle of Apollo. Things were going so fast, something changed.
Dialogue: 1,0:35:48.12,0:35:57.20,英黑,,0,0,0,,As a joke, I did not know this, and I'm just telling you this not to bring the room down, but I just want you to know that this happened.
Dialogue: 1,0:35:57.57,0:36:04.80,英黑,,0,0,0,,As a joke, before at the end of one of the meetings, the Apollo astronauts, they talk to the photographer,
Dialogue: 1,0:36:04.83,0:36:09.61,英黑,,0,0,0,,they're like, Hey, we got to do one more joke. We're going to play a joke on Shea.
Dialogue: 1,0:36:09.84,0:36:16.62,英黑,,0,0,0,,We want a picture of us with praying hands around our capsule.
Dialogue: 1,0:36:16.65,0:36:24.69,英黑,,0,0,0,,We want to say, and they said down there, on the note, they said, It isn't that we don't trust you, Joe, but this time we've decided to go over your head.
Dialogue: 1,0:36:24.72,0:36:30.76,英黑,,0,0,0,,They were jokingly saying, We all know there's problems here, and we're just, man, we're not feeling good about it.
Dialogue: 1,0:36:30.76,0:36:36.89,英黑,,0,0,0,,At the same time, to be clear, the Apollo astronauts, these gentlemen, they knew the risk
Dialogue: 1,0:36:36.89,0:36:41.12,英黑,,0,0,0,,and they didn't say something to the point where they're like, We got to fix it.
Dialogue: 1,0:36:41.12,0:36:43.13,英黑,,0,0,0,,I don't know what happened. I don't know what happened.
Dialogue: 1,0:36:43.89,0:36:49.46,英黑,,0,0,0,,All I know is that an engineering mistake happened and it wasn't caught.
Dialogue: 1,0:36:49.48,0:36:52.58,英黑,,0,0,0,,That's going to happen because we're humans and we're imperfect.
Dialogue: 1,0:36:52.61,0:36:58.21,英黑,,0,0,0,,But when that happened, what I do know is NASA changed, changed completely.
Dialogue: 1,0:36:58.24,0:37:04.34,英黑,,0,0,0,,The way they did things, like there were conversations that happened, and I'll go through that here in a minute.
Dialogue: 1,0:37:04.37,0:37:06.94,英黑,,0,0,0,,Here's something to think about.
Dialogue: 1,0:37:06.97,0:37:12.02,英黑,,0,0,0,,You guys like movies? Back to the future. It's pretty good one, right? Marty McFly, it's great.
Dialogue: 1,0:37:12.05,0:37:16.82,英黑,,0,0,0,,One of the cool things about those time travel movies is
Dialogue: 1,0:37:16.85,0:37:26.58,英黑,,0,0,0,,they'll go back in time and they're like, Oh, man, I can't change things because of how crazily I will influence the timeline of the future.
Dialogue: 1,0:37:26.85,0:37:34.76,英黑,,0,0,0,,If I move this bottle and the wrong person, whatever, I might not even be born.
Dialogue: 1,0:37:35.08,0:37:38.10,英黑,,0,0,0,,These little changes have monumental impacts.
Dialogue: 1,0:37:38.13,0:37:43.62,英黑,,0,0,0,,Primer By the way, a really good time travel movie, if you haven't watched it, Primer, really good.
Dialogue: 1,0:37:43.64,0:37:49.74,英黑,,0,0,0,,You've never heard of it. Budget for that movie was 7,000 bucks. Watch Primer, it's amazing. Great plot.
Dialogue: 1,0:37:49.77,0:37:53.82,英黑,,0,0,0,,These time travel movies, they can teach us something.
Dialogue: 1,0:37:53.85,0:38:01.10,英黑,,0,0,0,,Why do we not realize that we have that much control over the future now?
Dialogue: 1,0:38:01.13,0:38:05.51,英黑,,0,0,0,,Right now, you have that much control over the future as you're sitting there.
Dialogue: 1,0:38:06.09,0:38:11.13,英黑,,0,0,0,,Oh, man, if I were just to send this email and say this thing in a compelling way
Dialogue: 1,0:38:11.16,0:38:16.26,英黑,,0,0,0,,and impact the way the program reviews go and the CDR is coming up,
Dialogue: 1,0:38:16.26,0:38:21.26,英黑,,0,0,0,,if I could just get them to understand that Eclus needs to blah, blah, blah,
Dialogue: 1,0:38:21.29,0:38:25.94,英黑,,0,0,0,,why don't we have that level of gravitas to what we think about now?
Dialogue: 1,0:38:25.96,0:38:27.86,英黑,,0,0,0,,I just think that's cool, something to think about.
Dialogue: 1,0:38:27.88,0:38:29.42,英黑,,0,0,0,,Has anyone ever heard of this document?
Dialogue: 1,0:38:31.29,0:38:33.06,英黑,,0,0,0,,Don't raise your hand. Don't raise your hand.
Dialogue: 1,0:38:33.08,0:38:34.78,英黑,,0,0,0,,Does everybody remember the scoreboard earlier?
Dialogue: 1,0:38:35.66,0:38:44.77,英黑,,0,0,0,,Okay, so if I'm not mistaken, this room is full of people that are industry leaders that are in charge of taking humans back to the moon.
Dialogue: 1,0:38:45.33,0:38:54.73,英黑,,0,0,0,,Okay, in your head, don't raise your hand, in your head, answer the following question, have I read NASA SP 287?
Dialogue: 1,0:38:55.09,0:39:00.30,英黑,,0,0,0,,The title of the document is what made Apollo a success?
Dialogue: 1,0:39:00.68,0:39:02.17,英黑,,0,0,0,,Have you read it?
Dialogue: 1,0:39:02.41,0:39:05.91,英黑,,0,0,0,,And if you have not read it, I'm not joking about this,
Dialogue: 1,0:39:06.02,0:39:08.17,英黑,,0,0,0,,shame on you.
Dialogue: 1,0:39:08.28,0:39:09.52,英黑,,0,0,0,,Seriously.
Dialogue: 1,0:39:10.20,0:39:18.42,英黑,,0,0,0,,You have a whole generation of engineers that did the coolest thing engineering humans have ever done, and they gave you the playbook.
Dialogue: 1,0:39:18.65,0:39:20.48,英黑,,0,0,0,,They wrote it. All you got to do is read it.
Dialogue: 1,0:39:20.51,0:39:24.18,英黑,,0,0,0,,I've read it. I'm not even in your food chain. I don't even... I've read this thing.
Dialogue: 1,0:39:24.52,0:39:29.45,英黑,,0,0,0,,Granted, I read it really, really fast, so I could say I read it for effect, but I read it. [Audience Laughs]
Dialogue: 1,0:39:29.68,0:39:33.36,英黑,,0,0,0,,I made highlighting things in here. I want to go through some of this with you.
Dialogue: 1,0:39:33.36,0:39:37.80,英黑,,0,0,0,,Imagine the scoreboard. You've got the people that actually went to the moon.
Dialogue: 1,0:39:38.72,0:39:42.65,英黑,,0,0,0,,If they handed you the playbook and they're like, Hey, this is how you do it.
Dialogue: 1,0:39:42.68,0:39:44.03,英黑,,0,0,0,,This is the key.
Dialogue: 1,0:39:44.35,0:39:47.17,英黑,,0,0,0,,Seems pretty important. This exists.
Dialogue: 1,0:39:47.20,0:39:50.13,英黑,,0,0,0,,It's crazy that you don't know that if you don't know that this exists.
Dialogue: 1,0:39:50.16,0:39:52.65,英黑,,0,0,0,,Okay, it's really fun to read, by the way.
Dialogue: 1,0:39:52.68,0:40:00.10,英黑,,0,0,0,,It's written by several people that were over different things like trajectory calculations. Jean Krantz writes a section.
Dialogue: 1,0:40:00.12,0:40:03.06,英黑,,0,0,0,,It's a lot of really good stuff, but let's just read some of them.
Dialogue: 1,0:40:03.06,0:40:14.71,英黑,,0,0,0,,Of course, the way we got this job done was with meetings. Big meetings, little meetings, hundreds of meetings. The thing we always tried to do in these meetings was to encourage everyone, no matter how shy, to speak out,
Dialogue: 1,0:40:14.71,0:40:23.08,英黑,,0,0,0,,hopefully, but not always, without being subjected to ridicule. We wanted to make sure we had not overlooked any legitimate input.
Dialogue: 1,0:40:23.81,0:40:25.26,英黑,,0,0,0,,That's how you feel now.
Dialogue: 1,0:40:25.28,0:40:28.17,英黑,,0,0,0,,But I don't know, a lot of people are scared to talk today.
Dialogue: 1,0:40:28.20,0:40:29.92,英黑,,0,0,0,,Seems like they might have had a little different culture.
Dialogue: 1,0:40:30.12,0:40:32.42,英黑,,0,0,0,,All right, so spacecraft design, I thought this was interesting.
Dialogue: 1,0:40:32.45,0:40:38.00,英黑,,0,0,0,,It talks about how a spacecraft designing it, you have elements of missiles and aircraft.
Dialogue: 1,0:40:38.00,0:40:42.62,英黑,,0,0,0,,I've never designed a spacecraft, but I've worked with both aircraft and missile design.
Dialogue: 1,0:40:42.65,0:40:44.46,英黑,,0,0,0,,I feel like I get that.
Dialogue: 1,0:40:44.49,0:40:50.94,英黑,,0,0,0,,It says, and this is key, please hear this, this is the key to how to build your spacecraft.
Dialogue: 1,0:40:50.97,0:40:57.62,英黑,,0,0,0,,Build it simple and then double up on as many components or systems so that if one fails, the other will take over.
Dialogue: 1,0:40:57.93,0:41:07.86,英黑,,0,0,0,,Examples are a blade of thrust chambers that don't require regenerative cooling, hypergolic propellants that don't require Ignition source, three fuel cells, and that goes on and on.
Dialogue: 1,0:41:08.13,0:41:17.58,英黑,,0,0,0,,I was blown away to learn that the ascent stage in the current design does not use hypergolic propellants.
Dialogue: 1,0:41:17.60,0:41:18.74,英黑,,0,0,0,,That blew my mind.
Dialogue: 1,0:41:18.74,0:41:24.50,英黑,,0,0,0,,I was like, Wait, so we're going up there and we got to ignite this. I get it.
Dialogue: 1,0:41:24.52,0:41:28.30,英黑,,0,0,0,,You want to use in situ and you want to do methane. I got it, I understand.
Dialogue: 1,0:41:28.49,0:41:30.95,英黑,,0,0,0,,But hypergols always work.
Dialogue: 1,0:41:31.32,0:41:34.17,英黑,,0,0,0,,You make them touch and they go, Boom, that's how it works.
Dialogue: 1,0:41:34.20,0:41:38.00,英黑,,0,0,0,,I just thought it was interesting. I was like, We're changing.
Dialogue: 1,0:41:38.29,0:41:39.46,英黑,,0,0,0,,Is that good?
Dialogue: 1,0:41:39.49,0:41:42.49,英黑,,0,0,0,,Why are we introducing complexity into a system?
Dialogue: 1,0:41:42.72,0:41:44.46,英黑,,0,0,0,,I thought that was really, really interesting.
Dialogue: 1,0:41:44.66,0:41:47.65,英黑,,0,0,0,,This was an amazing chart.
Dialogue: 1,0:41:47.89,0:41:59.06,英黑,,0,0,0,,This chart, the person that wrote this, this was in the first chapter, the guy that wrote this, or the lady that wrote this, I forget, George M. Lowe wrote this.
Dialogue: 1,0:41:59.34,0:42:04.38,英黑,,0,0,0,,Do we know George Lowe? Is this good or bad? I don't know. I'm ignorant. That's good? Okay.
Dialogue: 1,0:42:04.50,0:42:05.90,英黑,,0,0,0,,You can tell how ignorant I am.
Dialogue: 1,0:42:05.92,0:42:10.02,英黑,,0,0,0,,This is great. I'm a third-party observer. I could leave and you guys have to deal with what I said.
Dialogue: 1,0:42:10.05,0:42:17.21,英黑,,0,0,0,,All right, so George Lowe said this, this is how they planned out what missions they were going to do when.
Dialogue: 1,0:42:17.49,0:42:25.26,英黑,,0,0,0,,They said too small a step would have involved the risk that is always inherent in manned space flight without any significant gain,
Dialogue: 1,0:42:25.26,0:42:36.46,英黑,,0,0,0,,without any real progress towards the lunar landing. Too large of a step, on the other hand, might have stretched the system beyond the capability and to the point where risk would have become excessive
Dialogue: 1,0:42:36.46,0:42:42.80,英黑,,0,0,0,,because the new requirements in flight operations were more than people could learn and practice and perfect in available time.
Dialogue: 1,0:42:42.83,0:42:45.65,英黑,,0,0,0,,Basically, you don't take baby steps,
Dialogue: 1,0:42:45.68,0:42:50.70,英黑,,0,0,0,,you take significant steps because you actually have to go towards the goal and there will be risk involved,
Dialogue: 1,0:42:50.87,0:42:56.44,英黑,,0,0,0,,but you make sure that the risk isn't too big so that the engineers on the ground can't learn the lessons.
Dialogue: 1,0:42:56.54,0:43:00.46,英黑,,0,0,0,,I thought that was brilliant. That's amazing. I've never read anything like that.
Dialogue: 1,0:43:00.49,0:43:06.85,英黑,,0,0,0,,I've worked on developing vehicles and active protection systems and counter missile systems.
Dialogue: 1,0:43:07.33,0:43:09.72,英黑,,0,0,0,,That was so succinct. It was amazing.
Dialogue: 1,0:43:09.75,0:43:12.11,英黑,,0,0,0,,Then I looked at Artemis III,
Dialogue: 1,0:43:13.17,0:43:18.17,英黑,,0,0,0,,to be clear, this is after Artemis II, which is about to happen.
Dialogue: 1,0:43:18.77,0:43:29.14,英黑,,0,0,0,,On Artemis III, in order for this to work, it starts, up at the beginning, it starts or anyway,
Dialogue: 1,0:43:29.95,0:43:33.14,英黑,,0,0,0,,we've never done cryogenic refueling in orbit.
Dialogue: 1,0:43:33.37,0:43:34.78,英黑,,0,0,0,,Humans have not done that.
Dialogue: 1,0:43:35.32,0:43:38.14,英黑,,0,0,0,,Am I wrong about that? Somebody correct me. Am I wrong about that?
Dialogue: 1,0:43:39.68,0:43:46.30,英黑,,0,0,0,,Okay, let that sink in. Humans have never done cryogenic refueling in orbit up to this point right now.
Dialogue: 1,0:43:47.88,0:43:51.70,英黑,,0,0,0,,Make all the charts you want, but we need to take some steps.
Dialogue: 1,0:43:51.72,0:43:56.14,英黑,,0,0,0,,I don't know how you guys are doing your programs, but I think this is very, very interesting.
Dialogue: 1,0:43:56.40,0:44:03.25,英黑,,0,0,0,,I think it's important for you guys to talk about this with authority because you're smart and you know things.
Dialogue: 1,0:44:03.47,0:44:08.70,英黑,,0,0,0,,All right, don't get fixated on technology demonstration. Focus on the mission.
Dialogue: 1,0:44:09.09,0:44:11.22,英黑,,0,0,0,,Focus on the mission. Focus on the mission.
Dialogue: 1,0:44:11.60,0:44:17.83,英黑,,0,0,0,,I sound arrogant right now, don't I? Please understand. I'm trying to be the voice of the 60s engineers, at least that's what I'm going to tell myself.
Dialogue: 1,0:44:17.94,0:44:20.06,英黑,,0,0,0,,What is the mission?
Dialogue: 1,0:44:21.95,0:44:25.32,英黑,,0,0,0,,Some really cool people. Really, really cool people.
Dialogue: 1,0:44:25.52,0:44:26.62,英黑,,0,0,0,,These folks are awesome.
Dialogue: 1,0:44:26.65,0:44:31.97,英黑,,0,0,0,,If you've ever met any of them, you know they are legitimately awesome people. They really are.
Dialogue: 1,0:44:32.33,0:44:40.40,英黑,,0,0,0,,My advice, and it's not my advice, it's through the generation of my grandfather, is keep it simple.
Dialogue: 1,0:44:40.97,0:44:47.71,英黑,,0,0,0,,As simple as you can make it and accomplish the mission, that's what we should be doing.
Dialogue: 1,0:44:48.05,0:44:50.44,英黑,,0,0,0,,We should make it as simple as possible.
Dialogue: 1,0:44:51.89,0:44:59.75,英黑,,0,0,0,,If you go through the old Apollo books, have you ever looked at how they decided to get the Lunar Lander off the moon, the ascent stage?
Dialogue: 1,0:45:01.01,0:45:04.18,英黑,,0,0,0,,Like, it's crazy because it's awesome.
Dialogue: 1,0:45:04.20,0:45:07.20,英黑,,0,0,0,,They're like, All right, so we're going to get the timing right and we're going to launch.
Dialogue: 1,0:45:07.23,0:45:13.64,英黑,,0,0,0,,That doesn't work because things aren't whatevering. Here's what we're going to do. You can read this in the stuff.
Dialogue: 1,0:45:13.67,0:45:17.74,英黑,,0,0,0,,They say, All right, if all else fails, here's what you do.
Dialogue: 1,0:45:17.77,0:45:20.90,英黑,,0,0,0,,Open the hatch, go around the back.
Dialogue: 1,0:45:21.13,0:45:26.11,英黑,,0,0,0,,There's these guillotines that connect the decent and the asset stage.
Dialogue: 1,0:45:26.41,0:45:29.77,英黑,,0,0,0,,You had to flip a switch and it would cut the guillotines.
Dialogue: 1,0:45:29.95,0:45:34.79,英黑,,0,0,0,,They would cut them loose and they would be disconnected and ready to hit the motor and go up.
Dialogue: 1,0:45:34.96,0:45:39.26,英黑,,0,0,0,,If that didn't work for whatever reason, they wrote a procedure. They're like, All right, here's the deal.
Dialogue: 1,0:45:39.29,0:45:47.24,英黑,,0,0,0,,Dude on the left or dude on the right. Whoever has the best integrity of their suit at the time, the least amount of leaks,
Dialogue: 1,0:45:47.24,0:45:54.44,英黑,,0,0,0,,you're going to depressurize, you're going to get out of the spacecraft, you're going to go to the bottom of the spacecraft with bolt cutters.
Dialogue: 1,0:45:55.64,0:45:57.58,英黑,,0,0,0,,It's awesome. It's great.
Dialogue: 1,0:45:57.61,0:46:04.94,英黑,,0,0,0,,With bolt cutters, and you're going to cut the straps that are holding the ascend and the decent stage together.
Dialogue: 1,0:46:05.09,0:46:08.21,英黑,,0,0,0,,That's like the sixth thing down.
Dialogue: 1,0:46:08.24,0:46:12.14,英黑,,0,0,0,,They tried this, okay, that worked. What if it doesn't work? Okay, we're going to go to this.
Dialogue: 1,0:46:12.37,0:46:14.38,英黑,,0,0,0,,Okay, then we're going to go to this.
Dialogue: 1,0:46:14.41,0:46:20.74,英黑,,0,0,0,,They had redundancy after redundancy after redundancy after redundancy all the way down to the bolt cutters.
Dialogue: 1,0:46:20.96,0:46:25.72,英黑,,0,0,0,,Harrison Schmitt said there was one thing after this. I just want to know what that was. [Audience Laughs]
Dialogue: 1,0:46:25.86,0:46:29.02,英黑,,0,0,0,,What is that? That's amazing.
Dialogue: 1,0:46:29.05,0:46:32.40,英黑,,0,0,0,,Are we building that level of redundancy into today's systems?
Dialogue: 1,0:46:32.40,0:46:35.29,英黑,,0,0,0,,Go look at the documents. This is a real thing.
Dialogue: 1,0:46:44.80,0:46:48.71,英黑,,0,0,0,,All right, so [Audience Laughs] PID control loop.
Dialogue: 1,0:46:49.40,0:46:51.95,英黑,,0,0,0,,Positive and negative feedback is important.
Dialogue: 1,0:46:52.80,0:46:56.79,英黑,,0,0,0,,As the engineers responsible for getting humans to the moon safely and returning them,
Dialogue: 1,0:46:56.79,0:47:05.52,英黑,,0,0,0,,our friends, it is imperative that you provide negative feedback in situations that call for it, and you are not scared to do so.
Dialogue: 1,0:47:05.55,0:47:11.36,英黑,,0,0,0,,If you lose your job for providing negative feedback, good on you.
Dialogue: 1,0:47:12.68,0:47:18.13,英黑,,0,0,0,,If it needed to be said and nobody said it, that would be the worst thing to live with.
Dialogue: 1,0:47:18.47,0:47:22.58,英黑,,0,0,0,,Make sure you're speaking up. Be bold, be courteous.
Dialogue: 1,0:47:22.69,0:47:25.82,英黑,,0,0,0,,Once a decision has been made, let's all get behind it and let's fight.
Dialogue: 1,0:47:26.44,0:47:27.72,英黑,,0,0,0,,But at the same time, let's be smart.
Dialogue: 1,0:47:27.75,0:47:33.26,英黑,,0,0,0,,Other things that we have the architecture we have, let's make it work. I put some inspiring slides in there.
Dialogue: 1,0:47:33.29,0:47:37.36,英黑,,0,0,0,,All right, so you have a limited amount of time at this point to simplify.
Dialogue: 1,0:47:37.39,0:47:41.98,英黑,,0,0,0,,We've chosen the architecture, we know what we're going to do.
Dialogue: 1,0:47:43.04,0:47:45.14,英黑,,0,0,0,,There's a little bit of wiggle room right now, right?
Dialogue: 1,0:47:45.52,0:47:48.27,英黑,,0,0,0,,We've got some play. Not a lot, but we've got some play.
Dialogue: 1,0:47:48.64,0:47:51.18,英黑,,0,0,0,,There are different things that you can choose and you can change.
Dialogue: 1,0:47:51.21,0:47:53.36,英黑,,0,0,0,,Make sure that you're making the right decisions.
Dialogue: 1,0:47:53.52,0:47:56.29,英黑,,0,0,0,,Focus on redundancy. Now, I'm going to go back to this document.
Dialogue: 1,0:47:56.84,0:48:01.74,英黑,,0,0,0,,Everybody take a note. This is NASA, SP 287. This is your homework.
Dialogue: 1,0:48:01.77,0:48:08.30,英黑,,0,0,0,,If you do not read this document, I will think bad things about you until you do.
Dialogue: 1,0:48:08.32,0:48:12.50,英黑,,0,0,0,,There you go. There's a guy out there somewhere thinking bad things about you until you read this document.
Dialogue: 1,0:48:12.64,0:48:18.14,英黑,,0,0,0,,Some things I learned from this document that I'll paraphrase, paraphrase as mine, focus on redundancy.
Dialogue: 1,0:48:18.17,0:48:23.42,英黑,,0,0,0,,This is the ascent motor. Lots of valves do similar things. Really cool design.
Dialogue: 1,0:48:23.65,0:48:25.30,英黑,,0,0,0,,Tests are the key.
Dialogue: 1,0:48:25.33,0:48:28.42,英黑,,0,0,0,,This blew my mind. This chart's in here.
Dialogue: 1,0:48:28.45,0:48:33.06,英黑,,0,0,0,,They tested stuff, vibrational modes, triaxial acceleration tests.
Dialogue: 1,0:48:33.08,0:48:36.34,英黑,,0,0,0,,They tested stuff and they shook it. You know what they found?
Dialogue: 1,0:48:36.37,0:48:48.14,英黑,,0,0,0,,5% of the stuff broke because of how they did it. 1.5% on the left was due to the design of the component. 3.5% was workmanship for a total of 5% of the stuff.
Dialogue: 1,0:48:48.29,0:48:50.70,英黑,,0,0,0,,This is just a representative of these stuff.
Dialogue: 1,0:48:50.73,0:48:56.92,英黑,,0,0,0,,But they explained why and they're like, Hey, there's going to be mishaps because we're humans and all the workmanship is not going to be perfect.
Dialogue: 1,0:48:56.92,0:49:00.24,英黑,,0,0,0,,You need to know it's there, need to go find it. The way you find it is test.
Dialogue: 1,0:49:00.51,0:49:03.21,英黑,,0,0,0,,I thought it was brilliant, man. This is an awesome document.
Dialogue: 1,0:49:03.24,0:49:05.01,英黑,,0,0,0,,Don't compromise on your standards.
Dialogue: 1,0:49:05.01,0:49:09.78,英黑,,0,0,0,,Let me tell you what's going to happen. I've given enough briefings at the Pentagon.
Dialogue: 1,0:49:09.80,0:49:12.67,英黑,,0,0,0,,Young engineers, if you haven't done that yet, you're going to do it and this is what's going to happen.
Dialogue: 1,0:49:12.67,0:49:17.42,英黑,,0,0,0,,You're going to get in that room and you're going to tell them, We can't do this and we can't do this because of that.
Dialogue: 1,0:49:17.45,0:49:20.14,英黑,,0,0,0,,They're going to say, But my schedule says this.
Dialogue: 1,0:49:20.17,0:49:26.88,英黑,,0,0,0,,You're like, If you do this, then you just have to be willing to say the truth.
Dialogue: 1,0:49:27.06,0:49:31.50,英黑,,0,0,0,,Sometimes the manager is going to accept the risk and that's okay.
Dialogue: 1,0:49:31.52,0:49:37.38,英黑,,0,0,0,,You mitigate the risk as far as you can. You communicate clearly, but you make sure you don't compromise on standards.
Dialogue: 1,0:49:37.40,0:49:42.39,英黑,,0,0,0,,The one thing that always happened is people tried to figure out how to delete tests from the test plan.
Dialogue: 1,0:49:42.61,0:49:43.95,英黑,,0,0,0,,Always happens.
Dialogue: 1,0:49:44.05,0:49:47.74,英黑,,0,0,0,,Oh, man, we're six months behind. How do we gain that schedule?
Dialogue: 1,0:49:47.77,0:49:50.48,英黑,,0,0,0,,We delete that test that takes eight months.
Dialogue: 1,0:49:50.93,0:49:53.80,英黑,,0,0,0,,Sometimes that's smart. They did that in Apollo.
Dialogue: 1,0:49:54.15,0:50:00.76,英黑,,0,0,0,,After Apollo 8, they said in here that they were able to delete a couple of tests or a couple of shots, I forget what it was,
Dialogue: 1,0:50:00.76,0:50:08.06,英黑,,0,0,0,,but they saved a lot of time because there was one or two things they were able to mitigate the risk by cleverly designing experiments and they saved time. It's really cool.
Dialogue: 1,0:50:08.19,0:50:10.93,英黑,,0,0,0,,Crew training is paramount.
Dialogue: 1,0:50:11.67,0:50:14.94,英黑,,0,0,0,,I think I disagree with a lot of people on this one.
Dialogue: 1,0:50:14.97,0:50:25.64,英黑,,0,0,0,,I think, and I made a video about this on Smarter Every Day, the lunar lander test vehicle, for example, if you're going to land in a 1/6th-G environment, you have to know how to do that.
Dialogue: 1,0:50:26.36,0:50:29.34,英黑,,0,0,0,,Our pilots are used to walking around in 1G.
Dialogue: 1,0:50:29.34,0:50:35.21,英黑,,0,0,0,,There's a weird thing that happens. A helicopter doesn't behave the same in 1G as it does in 1/6th-G.
Dialogue: 1,0:50:35.24,0:50:42.14,英黑,,0,0,0,,Neil Armstrong had a really, really interesting talk about this at the test pilot conference one time.
Dialogue: 1,0:50:42.17,0:50:49.04,英黑,,0,0,0,,Anyway, long story short because of time, I found the engineer that helped design this thing, the Lunar Lander test vehicle.
Dialogue: 1,0:50:49.07,0:50:51.86,英黑,,0,0,0,,This is how they trained astronauts to land on the moon.
Dialogue: 1,0:50:52.82,0:50:54.21,英黑,,0,0,0,,I think it's important.
Dialogue: 1,0:50:54.48,0:50:59.90,英黑,,0,0,0,,The reason this is more important than a simulator is the astronaut in the seat, their life is on the line.
Dialogue: 1,0:51:00.39,0:51:01.54,英黑,,0,0,0,,That matters.
Dialogue: 1,0:51:01.57,0:51:06.94,英黑,,0,0,0,,When your blood pressure goes up and you're like, It matters. I have to get this right.
Dialogue: 1,0:51:06.97,0:51:09.98,英黑,,0,0,0,,That psychological training has a huge component.
Dialogue: 1,0:51:10.12,0:51:16.83,英黑,,0,0,0,,I spoke to a man named Dr, not Dr. Mr. Otinger, who worked on the control system, and I asked him a very important question.
Dialogue: 1,0:51:17.00,0:51:20.80,英黑,,0,0,0,,I said, Well, I'll just let you hear it. Maybe I can get this right. Let's see what happens.
Dialogue: 1,0:51:21.07,0:51:25.38,英黑,,0,0,0,,But I would like to ask you two more questions, and these are big picture questions.
Dialogue: 1,0:51:25.41,0:51:35.04,英黑,,0,0,0,,So back in the day, the engineers and scientists on this program did amazing things with limited- Analog electronics. Right. He said analog electronics.
Dialogue: 1,0:51:35.07,0:51:42.56,英黑,,0,0,0,,So do you think that engineers in the '50s and '60s were better than engineers today?
Dialogue: 1,0:51:42.86,0:51:45.23,英黑,,0,0,0,,No. No.
Dialogue: 1,0:51:45.23,0:51:55.66,英黑,,0,0,0,,I think we all had our unique place in history and they'll continue to be new challenges met.
Dialogue: 1,0:51:55.69,0:51:58.82,英黑,,0,0,0,,There'll be innovation that continues.
Dialogue: 1,0:51:58.85,0:52:02.81,英黑,,0,0,0,,In part of it is because they can build on our shoulders.
Dialogue: 1,0:52:03.58,0:52:09.94,英黑,,0,0,0,,They can learn from what we did and adapt to the new technology and so forth.
Dialogue: 1,0:52:09.96,0:52:14.70,英黑,,0,0,0,,Do you think something like the LLTV needs to happen to train astronauts to go back to the moon?
Dialogue: 1,0:52:14.96,0:52:19.34,英黑,,0,0,0,,They aren't going to go if they don't get a trainer, a free-flight trainer, I can tell you that.
Dialogue: 1,0:52:19.49,0:52:22.32,英黑,,0,0,0,,Really? Yeah, they won't go without it.
Dialogue: 1,0:52:22.86,0:52:25.90,英黑,,0,0,0,,They're smart enough to know.
Dialogue: 1,0:52:25.93,0:52:31.16,英黑,,0,0,0,,Now the United States is planning to return to the moon. Neil Armstrong.
Dialogue: 1,0:52:31.19,0:52:35.86,英黑,,0,0,0,,The aircraft is on final approach to that flat tip ridge near Shackleton Crater.
Dialogue: 1,0:52:35.89,0:52:47.10,英黑,,0,0,0,,I hope that the person at the controls has a simulation experience that is at least as good as the LLTV provided the Apollo crews a half century later.
Dialogue: 1,0:52:47.13,0:52:48.94,英黑,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 1,0:52:49.58,0:52:51.30,英黑,,0,0,0,,I thought that was really interesting.
Dialogue: 1,0:52:51.33,0:52:54.62,英黑,,0,0,0,,The older generation believes in you. He said it.
Dialogue: 1,0:52:54.65,0:52:59.47,英黑,,0,0,0,,I said, Do you think the Apollo engineers were smarter than the engineers are today?
Dialogue: 1,0:52:59.55,0:53:10.20,英黑,,0,0,0,,I think a lot of us today, we maybe think that about ourselves a little bit, like, Well, we got so many tools, we don't know how to do differential equations like they did by hand.
Dialogue: 1,0:53:11.26,0:53:16.46,英黑,,0,0,0,,I think that. I don't know if you do. It was really encouraging to hear him say that.
Dialogue: 1,0:53:16.49,0:53:23.19,英黑,,0,0,0,,He said, No. The way he said it was so interesting. No, we're not better than they are.
Dialogue: 1,0:53:23.19,0:53:26.36,英黑,,0,0,0,,It's different and they're going to build on our shoulders.
Dialogue: 1,0:53:28.08,0:53:31.70,英黑,,0,0,0,,Here's the deal. There's a scoreboard, it exists.
Dialogue: 1,0:53:32.49,0:53:35.30,英黑,,0,0,0,,Apollo engineers, six lunar landings, Artemis Zero.
Dialogue: 1,0:53:36.17,0:53:39.98,英黑,,0,0,0,,It's time to put points on the board and they've given you the playbook.
Dialogue: 1,0:53:41.52,0:53:47.85,英黑,,0,0,0,,The playbook is called What made Apollo a success. Sp 287.
Dialogue: 1,0:53:48.17,0:53:57.22,英黑,,0,0,0,,I would encourage you to read it if you haven't. We do not need to have an Apollo 1 type of event in order to get us in gear.
Dialogue: 1,0:53:57.47,0:54:01.02,英黑,,0,0,0,,Don't get fixated on a technology demonstration.
Dialogue: 1,0:54:01.04,0:54:06.61,英黑,,0,0,0,,Just because we can do something new and sexy and awesome and amazing and wild, doesn't mean you have to.
Dialogue: 1,0:54:06.71,0:54:08.04,英黑,,0,0,0,,Simple is good.
Dialogue: 1,0:54:08.17,0:54:14.94,英黑,,0,0,0,,As long as it accomplishes the mission. So be mission-focused, and I think things are going to be okay.
Dialogue: 1,0:54:15.06,0:54:25.02,英黑,,0,0,0,,All right, so here's the thing that happens. Sometimes our thinking can get locked in on a thing, and it's like bias. We get biased on a thing.
Dialogue: 1,0:54:25.28,0:54:28.30,英黑,,0,0,0,,I'm going to tell you a story about how I got fixated on something.
Dialogue: 1,0:54:28.30,0:54:33.31,英黑,,0,0,0,,Whatever you're doing in your job to get people back to the moon or Mars or whatever your job is,
Dialogue: 1,0:54:33.66,0:54:38.71,英黑,,0,0,0,,don't get fixated on the way people have told you it has to be, and this is why.
Dialogue: 1,0:54:38.71,0:54:44.38,英黑,,0,0,0,,A long time ago, my buddy, Barney, he's a welder, he said, Hey, Destin, come on down to the weld shop.
Dialogue: 1,0:54:44.38,0:54:47.57,英黑,,0,0,0,,This was down at the missile range. Barney had built this bicycle.
Dialogue: 1,0:54:47.85,0:54:50.66,英黑,,0,0,0,,It's a really... Dad, can I see that real quick?
Dialogue: 1,0:54:51.06,0:54:58.04,英黑,,0,0,0,,Barney had taken a normal bicycle and he had flipped it around. Check this out. Thanks.
Dialogue: 1,0:54:58.18,0:55:02.14,英黑,,0,0,0,,It's my dad. He's awesome. [Audience Applause]
Dialogue: 1,0:55:02.65,0:55:06.94,英黑,,0,0,0,,Okay. This bike, it's really cool. It's like a transformer.
Dialogue: 1,0:55:06.97,0:55:13.46,英黑,,0,0,0,,Basically, this thing, when you turn the handlebar to the left, it goes to the right.
Dialogue: 1,0:55:14.53,0:55:19.00,英黑,,0,0,0,,How many variables have I changed? Changed one variable.
Dialogue: 1,0:55:19.03,0:55:20.90,英黑,,0,0,0,,Does everybody in the room know how that thing works?
Dialogue: 1,0:55:22.12,0:55:27.72,英黑,,0,0,0,,It was really, really difficult for me to learn how to ride that thing. This is the first time I was on it.
Dialogue: 1,0:55:29.99,0:55:33.14,英黑,,0,0,0,,The faster I go the better.
Dialogue: 1,0:55:34.53,0:55:36.02,英黑,,0,0,0,,I couldn't do it.
Dialogue: 1,0:55:36.17,0:55:39.22,英黑,,0,0,0,,You can see that I'm laughing, but I'm actually really frustrated.
Dialogue: 1,0:55:39.45,0:55:42.50,英黑,,0,0,0,,In this moment, I had a really deep revelation.
Dialogue: 1,0:55:42.69,0:55:44.63,英黑,,0,0,0,,My thinking was in a rut.
Dialogue: 1,0:55:44.81,0:55:47.58,英黑,,0,0,0,,This bike revealed a very deep truth to me.
Dialogue: 1,0:55:47.58,0:55:52.52,英黑,,0,0,0,,I had the knowledge of how to operate the bike, but I did not have the understanding.
Dialogue: 1,0:55:52.52,0:55:54.42,英黑,,0,0,0,,Okay, it's pretty interesting. Can one of you guys ride a bike?
Dialogue: 1,0:55:55.10,0:56:02.17,英黑,,0,0,0,,You can ride a bike? Can you help me for just a second? Yeah. All right. [Audience Applause]
Dialogue: 1,0:56:02.31,0:56:03.74,英黑,,0,0,0,,What's your name? Gabriel.
Dialogue: 1,0:56:03.77,0:56:07.90,英黑,,0,0,0,,Gabriel, we don't have an SOP, we don't have PPE, we don't have anything.
Dialogue: 1,0:56:08.31,0:56:12.46,英黑,,0,0,0,,We're just going to roll. All right, so here's what we're going to do. Gabriel, I don't want you to hurt yourself.
Dialogue: 1,0:56:12.48,0:56:15.06,英黑,,0,0,0,,You're wearing a suit. It's a very nice-looking suit.
Dialogue: 1,0:56:15.09,0:56:17.93,英黑,,0,0,0,,Do this. Go ahead and hop on this thing.
Dialogue: 1,0:56:19.94,0:56:22.82,英黑,,0,0,0,,It's going to do weird things to your brain, man, I promise.
Dialogue: 1,0:56:22.85,0:56:32.33,英黑,,0,0,0,,Just put your foot right there and then just try to ride, let's say, one, two, three, look, man, don't hurt yourself, okay?
