Dialogue: 1,0:56:59.16,0:57:03.27,英黑,,0,0,0,,Right? Thank you very much. Give it up for Gabriel. [Audience Applause]
Dialogue: 1,0:57:03.91,0:57:12.70,英黑,,0,0,0,,What's happening right now is you've got this way of thinking that you've grown up your whole life learning this way of thinking, and it's just natural.
Dialogue: 1,0:57:12.70,0:57:18.07,英黑,,0,0,0,,This is what I do. This is how I do the TPS report. This is how I do the whatever, right?
Dialogue: 1,0:57:18.69,0:57:23.84,英黑,,0,0,0,,It's so hard. I had to work to overcome my own brain at figuring this out.
Dialogue: 1,0:57:23.84,0:57:26.29,英黑,,0,0,0,,How long do you think it took me to learn how to ride this thing?
Dialogue: 1,0:57:26.65,0:57:31.22,英黑,,0,0,0,,Months. I did it for five minutes a day, and this is what that looks like when it finally worked.
Dialogue: 1,0:57:31.65,0:57:37.54,英黑,,0,0,0,,I couldn't ride the bike, and the next day I could. It was like I could feel some pathway in my brain that was now unlocked.
Dialogue: 1,0:57:37.56,0:57:40.52,英黑,,0,0,0,,It was really weird, though. It's like there's this trail in my brain.
Dialogue: 1,0:57:40.52,0:57:46.78,英黑,,0,0,0,,But if I wasn't paying close enough attention to it, my brain would easily lose that neural path and jump back onto the old road it was more familiar with.
Dialogue: 1,0:57:46.78,0:57:52.98,英黑,,0,0,0,,Any small distractions at all, like a cell phone ringing in my pocket, would instantly throw my brain back to the old control algorithm and I would wreck.
Dialogue: 1,0:57:52.98,0:57:54.70,英黑,,0,0,0,,But at least I could ride it.
